  "texts": [
    "When investigating movement synchrony with SIAs, time delay, and intensity are essential aspects that are carefully controlled by the proposed experimental toolkit.",
    "Controlling the time delay involves thoroughly understanding important parameters and the data and information processing pipeline.",
    "In the autonomous mode, a significant movement (e.g., head nodding) has to be detected by social signal classifiers before any observable animation as a reaction of the SIA is shown.",
    "Usually, there is a defined configurable movement threshold.",
    "The movement range (e.g., head tilt angle from 2 -10 degrees) correlates to the intensity (e.g., weak -strong head nodding)."
  ],
